  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Due to absence of Deceased-donors in Egypt, Living-donor liver transplantation (LDLT) has
      emerged as an option to the traditional deceased-donor transplantation procedure. But there
      is an essential risk related to liver resection for healthy donors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this work is to identify and analyze the causes of disqualification of potential
      Egyptian living liver-donors in a University based liver transplant program
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
